<br>
While grouped with a caster and a few others a couple of days ago our group got a pull of 3 sarnaks. Our caster (luckily not our only healer) decided in his infinite wisdom to dish out some melee damage. Of course he immediately started taking punishment. With his hit points down to less then one red cell I told him to back up. He did and the sarnaks turned to attack me (we were directly across from each other). Now here's where irony takes over. As he steps back he casts a spell which he thinks makes him invisible (although he never disappeared from my sight). Then in group speak he said &quot;Look guys they can't see me. Hahaha.&quot; and takes a step toward the sarnaks. At the same time he steps forward the sarnaks turn and take him down with one hit! The timing couldn't have been more perfect. When the fight was over I couldn't help but laugh as I saw him curled in the fetal position on the ground. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utranthas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tranthas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/01 2:21:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=760.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leave It To A Caster</span><hr size=1> Famous last words.<br>
<br>
